      "description": "VanEck Utilities TruSector ETF is an actively managed fund that seeks long-term capital appreciation by investing at least 80% of its total assets in equity securities of utilities-related companies, including electric utilities, gas utilities, multi-utilities, water utilities, and independent power producers and energy traders. As part of VanEck's TruSector suite, the Fund is designed to deliver full market-cap sector exposure rather than the underweighted largest-holdings exposure typical of traditional sector funds constrained by Registered Investment Company (RIC) diversification rules, offering closer alignment with how the broader market actually defines and weights the Utilities sector.",
